# ║  WHY: During the March 2026 security lockdown (Issue #3), it was       ║
# ║  identified that agents were making unauthorized structural changes    ║
# ║  to repository configuration files — including .gitignore — without    ║
# ║  user knowledge or consent. This enables files to be hidden from       ║
# ║  tracking, which is a security risk.                                   ║
# ║                                                                        ║
# ║  VIOLATION: Any unauthorized modification to this file will be         ║
# ║  treated as a security incident and the responsible agent/PR will      ║
